<div class="container">
  <div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 col-xs-12">
    <h1>Hello!!</h1>
    <p class="welcome">Welcome to my natural blog! If you're like me, you love making and crafting your stuff, like chapstick, or even laundry detergent!</p>
    <p class="welcome">However, if you're even more like me, then you're probably a little lazy and don't like the idea of having to purchase a bunch of stuff that you aren't familiar with, or have never heard of before.</p>
    <p class="welcome">That's where my blog comes in! I find the easiest, cheapest way to do all these things naturally!</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 col-xs-12">
    <% @posts.each do |post| %>
    <div class="col-xs-12 text-center">
      <div class="text-center">
        <h2><%= post.title %></h2>
        <h6><%= post.created_at.strftime('%b %d, %Y') %></h6>
      </div>
      <div>
        <%= raw(post.body).truncate(358) %>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <%= link_to "READ MORE", post_path(post) %>
      </div>
      <% if admin_signed_in? %>
        <%= link_to "Edit", edit_post_path(post), class: "btn btn-default" %>
        <%= link_to "Delete", post_path(post), class: "btn btn-danger", data: {:confirm => "Are you sure?"}, method: :delete %>
      <% end %>
      <hr />
    </div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>
